Police paid 18 times more for generators than their supplier, businessman Thoshan. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police paid more for generators than their supplier, businessman Thoshan Panday. That's the allegations made during a forensic auditor's testimony at the State Capture Commission of Inquiry on Monday. READ: Zondo lashes state capture legal team Panday's one of twelve suspects identified in a police investigation. The SAPS paid firms linked to him around R47-million in under a year. Proceedings continue on Tuesday.